# Claude Code per-developer state — entire .claude/ tree
.claude/
# …except test fixtures, which legitimately contain a `.claude/`
# subtree that mimics what a real Cowork session directory looks
# like on disk. These are synthetic (redacted), vital for the
# exporter's cowork-source unit + integration tests, and must be
# committed so CI can see them. Both the directories AND their
# contents need the negation — a gitignored parent would otherwise
# swallow the children regardless of a `!pattern/**` rule.
!packages/exporter/test/fixtures/**/.claude/
!packages/exporter/test/fixtures/**/.claude/**

# Exporter output for local dev — data is on user's machine, not in repo
apps/standalone/public/chat-arch-data/*
# Keep empty chat-arch-data dir on fresh clones.
!apps/standalone/public/chat-arch-data/.gitkeep

